description: Argentina and Colombia said they are moving towards amending frayed diplomatic relations in a joint statement published late on Sunday, following comments by libertarian Argentine President Javier Milei that had offended his leftist Colombian counterpart.
title: Argentina and Colombia to mend ties following Milei 'terrorist' comments

description: At least three people are missing after an avalanche rumbled down a mountain on Monday afternoon at Riffelberg by the Swiss Alpine ski resort of Zermatt, police said.
title: At least three missing after avalanche near Swiss resort of Zermatt

description: The Biden administration is weighing whether to go ahead with a major $18 billion package of arms transfers to Israel that would involve dozens of F-15 aircraft and munitions, three sources familiar with the matter said on Monday.
title: Biden administration weighing $18 billion in arms transfers to Israel, sources say

description: A blast ripped through a Central Asian-themed cafe in the Russian city of Voronezh on Monday, shattering windows, Russian news agencies reported, citing local police.
title: Blast rips through cafe in Russia's Voronezh, media report

description: The United Kingdom Maritime Trade Operations (UKMTO) agency said on Monday it received a report of an incident 150 nautical miles northwest of Yemen's Hodeidah.
title: British maritime agency receives report of incident off Yemen's Hodeidah

description: China views its relations with Indonesia from a strategic and long-term perspective and stands ready to deepen all-round strategic cooperation with the Southeast Asian nation, Chinese state media said on Monday, citing a meeting between leaders of the countries.
title: China ready to deepen strategic cooperation with Indonesia

description: Taiwan's outgoing President Tsai Ing-wen plans to flee in a U.S. plane if war erupts with China, according to an unsubstantiated report first published in 2021 and echoed in the run-up to the island's January 2024 general election.
title: Chinese state media stoked allegation Taiwan's president would flee war

description: An Indian court sent Delhi chief minister and key opposition leader Arvind Kejriwal to jail until April 15 in a liquor graft case on Monday, local media reported, less than three weeks before the country begins voting in national elections.
title: Delhi Chief Minister Kejriwal sent to jail until April 15 in graft case, media reports say

description: Democratic Republic of Congo's President Felix Tshisekedi on Monday appointed the country's first ever female prime minister, naming planning minister Judith Suminwa to the role.
title: DR Congo president appoints country's first female prime minister

description: President Tayyip Erdogan vowed on Monday to correct any mistakes that led to his party's defeat in Turkey's local elections where the opposition capitalised on economic woes and alienated Islamist voters, casting uncertainty over his reform plans.
title: Erdogan vows to make amends after humbling election loss in Turkey

description: Iran tipped off Russia about the possibility of a major "terrorist operation" on its soil ahead of the concert hall massacre near Moscow last month, three sources familiar with the matter said.
title: Exclusive: Iran alerted Russia to security threat before Moscow attack

description: A fire broke out on Monday at the Uralmash factory, a large heavy industry enterprise in the Russian city of Yekaterinburg, Russia's emergencies ministry said.
title: Fire breaks out at Uralmash factory in Russia's Yekaterinburg

description: Foreign fighters detained on Sunday in Russia's southern region of Dagestan were involved in financing a deadly attack on a concert hall near Moscow last month, the TASS news agency cited Russia's FSB state security service as saying on Monday.
title: Foreign fighters held in Russia's Dagestan linked to concert hall attack - TASS

description: Former Taiwan president Ma Ying-jeou left on Monday for an 11-day trip to China where he is expected next week to have his second meeting with Chinese President Xi Jinping, at a time of simmering tensions across the Taiwan Strait.
title: Former Taiwan president Ma leaves for China, likely to meet Xi

description: France on Monday proposed a draft United Nations Security Council resolution that seeks options for possible U.N. monitoring of a ceasefire in the Gaza Strip and proposals to help the Palestinian Authority assume responsibilities.
title: France seeks UN Security Council resolution for Gaza truce monitoring

description: Greece's conservative government promised on Monday to offer extra financial aid and more staff to help the island of Crete and its tiny neighbour Gavdos handle a steep rise in arrivals of migrants trying to cross to Europe from Libya.
title: Greece pledges to help islands of Crete, Gavdos handle surge in migrant arrivals

description: Five people were killed by falling trees as strong winds battered southern Poland on Monday, reaching a speed of 155 km (96 miles) an hour in the highest parts of the Tatra mountains.
title: High winds cause five deaths in south Poland

description: India on Monday put on hold a proposed hike in road toll charges, in a move that will be welcomed by millions of motorists, truckers and commercial vehicle owners just ahead of a general election.
title: India puts on hold proposed hike in road toll charges as elections approach

description: India's half-century-old decision to end a territorial dispute with Sri Lanka over a tiny island has become a hot-button election issue, with Prime Minister Narendra Modi's party accusing the rival Congress of compromising fishermen's rights.
title: India's Modi questions rival Congress about island ceded to Sri Lanka

description: India's Income Tax department will not pursue a 35-billion rupee ($420 million) payment from the main opposition Congress party until after the completion of general elections in June, the department told the country's top court on Monday.
title: India's opposition Congress gets breather from $420 mln tax payment until after elections

description: India is likely to experience more heat wave days than normal between April and June, the weather office said on Monday.
title: India's weather office forecasts more heat wave days during April-June

description: Bima Abdul Sholeh, 32, sat calmly as a doctor armed with a laser pointer zapped tattoos from his face at an event in Jakarta being held by a charity organisation during the holy month of Ramadan to give practicing Muslims an opportunity to "repent".
title: Indonesian Muslims sign up for tattoo removal 'to repent' during Ramadan

description: Indonesia's President-elect Prabowo Subianto is expected to meet Chinese President Xi Jinping in Beijing on Monday for high-level talks, less than two months after winning the race to lead Southeast Asia's biggest economy.
title: Indonesian president-elect visits China after decade of close ties

description: Indonesian financial regulator Mahendra Siregar and former finance minister Chatib Basri are among the top choices Prabowo Subianto is considering for the role of finance minister, sources close to the president-elect told Reuters.
title: Indonesia's Prabowo weighs former minister, regulator chief for finance job, sources say

description: Indonesia's President-elect Prabowo Subianto will visit Japan on April 2-3, where he is set to meet Prime Minister Fumio Kishida and other officials, Japan's chief cabinet secretary Yoshimasa Hayashi said on Monday.
title: Indonesia's President-elect Prabowo will visit Japan on April 2-3, Japan says

description: Israeli warplanes struck the Iranian consulate in Damascus on Monday, and a Lebanese security source told Reuters a senior commander of the Iranian Revolutionary Guards Corps, Mohammad Reza Zahedi, had been killed in the attack.
title: Iranian Guards commander killed in Israeli strike on consulate in Damascus, source says

description: Israeli warplanes struck the Iranian consulate in Damascus on Monday, and a Lebanese security source told Reuters a senior commander of the Iranian Revolutionary Guards Corps, Mohammad Reza Zahedi, had been killed in the attack.
title: Iranian Guards commander killed in Israeli strike on consulate in Damascus, source says

description: At least five employees from the World Central Kitchen (WCK) non-governmental organisation, including foreigners, were killed in an Israeli airstrike on Gaza, the Hamas-run Gaza government media office said late on Monday.
title: Israel airstrike on Gaza kills foreign aid workers, Hamas-run media office says

description: Suspected Israeli warplanes bombed Iran's embassy in Syria on Monday, a marked escalation in a war pitting Israel against its regional adversaries, and Tehran said the strike killed seven military advisers including three senior commanders.
title: Israel bombs Iran embassy in Syria, Iranian commanders among dead

description: An aerial threat launched from east of Israel struck a building in its Red Sea port of Eilat on Monday but did not cause casualties, the Israeli military said.
title: Israel says flying object from east hits Eilat, no casualties

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu was conscious and conversing with family on Monday after undergoing a successful hernia operation, the hospital treating him said.
title: Israeli PM Netanyahu’s hernia operation was successful, hospital says

description: Israeli forces have withdrawn from Gaza's Al Shifa Hospital after a two-week operation during which they killed Palestinian gunmen in clashes and seized weaponry and intelligence documents, the military said on Monday.
title: Israeli troops leave Gaza's Al Shifa Hospital after two-week sweep

description: The Kremlin on Monday dismissed a report that Russian military intelligence may be behind the mysterious "Havana syndrome" ailment that has afflicted U.S. diplomats and spies globally.
title: Kremlin dismisses report Russia behind 'Havana Syndrome'

description: A Republican and a Democratic member of Congress are calling on the Biden administration to add seven Chinese biotech firms to a list created by the Defense Department to highlight firms it says are allegedly working with Beijing's military.
title: Lawmakers urge Biden to call out more Chinese biotech firms

description: An earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 6.1 hit Iwate and Aomori prefectures in northern Japan on Tuesday, the Japan Meteorological Agency said.
title: Magnitude 6.1 earthquake strikes northern Japan

description: Political parties in Mali have requested a time frame for presidential elections after the ruling junta failed to organise polls within a promised 24-month transition back to democracy.
title: Mali political parties request elections after junta shuns transition promise

description: Moscow's Basmanny district court ruled on Monday that the 10th suspect in the March 22 deadly concert hall attack should be put into custody until May 22, pending trial, the court said on Telegram.
title: Moscow court puts 10th suspect in concert hall attack under pre-trial custody

description: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu revived moves on Monday to shut down Qatari satellite television station Al Jazeera in Israel, saying through his party spokesperson that parliament would be convened in the evening to ratify the necessary law.
title: Netanyahu revives moves to shut Qatar's Al Jazeera TV in Israel

description: North Korea fired a ballistic missile off the east coast, South Korea's military said on Tuesday.
title: North Korea fires ballistic missile, South Korea says

description: A Pakistani court on Monday granted former Prime Minister Imran Khan an appeal of his conviction for graft and suspended his 14-year jail sentence, his party said.
title: Pakistan court grants Imran Khan appeal of graft conviction, sentence suspended

description: The Palestinian Authority wants the United Nations Security Council to vote this month to make it a full member of the world body, the Palestinian U.N. envoy told Reuters on Monday, a move that can be blocked by Israel's ally the United States.
title: Palestinians want April vote for full United Nations membership

description: Panic set in around downtown Port-au-Prince on Monday as wild shooting filled the streets of Haiti's capital, with heavy gunfire approaching the national palace.
title: Panic in Haiti's capital as wild shooting fills streets

description: Peruvian Interior Minister Victor Torres announced his resignation to reporters on Monday amid a political scandal involving alleged illicit enrichment by the country's president, who is being investigated over use luxurious Rolex watches.
title: Peru interior minister steps down amid Rolex scandal

description: Countermeasures by the Philippines to China's conduct in the South China Sea will entail strengthening its defence capabilities with allies and exhausting all diplomatic measures to resolve disputes, a security official said on Monday.
title: Philippines to boost diplomacy and defence capability as South China Sea 'countermeasures'

description: Russia on Monday halted an operation aimed at saving 13 miners trapped in a mine since March 18, the TASS news agency cited mine management as saying.
title: Russia halts rescue operation for 13 trapped miners - TASS

description: Russia and Ukraine traded claims on Monday on downing enemy drones over the Black sea, with both sides apparently devoting increasing attention to developing and using unmanned aircraft.
title: Russia, Ukraine trade drone claims over Black Sea

description: A Russian court extended the pre-trial detention of Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty journalist Alsu Kurmasheva until June 5, a Reuters witness reported from the courtroom.
title: Russian court extends pre-trial detention of RFE/RL journalist

description: The mysterious "Havana syndrome" ailment that has afflicted U.S. diplomats and spies across the world may be linked to energy weapons wielded by members of a Russian military intelligence sabotage unit, the Insider media group reported.
title: Russian military intelligence unit may be linked to 'Havana syndrome', Insider reports

description: Beset by controversies about share price manipulation and a costly gifted handbag, South Korea's first lady has not been seen in public since Dec. 15, but few in Seoul were surprised as a high-stakes parliamentary election approaches this month.
title: South Korea's first lady avoids limelight ahead of high-stakes election

description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol said on Monday his government is open to talks with doctors who oppose his plan to increase medical school admissions, while accusing critics of offering no reasonable alternative to ease a doctor shortage.
title: South Korea's Yoon urges doctors to end impasse over trainees

description: Thousands of Israelis took to the streets in Jerusalem on Monday, continuing a three-day protest against the government of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and demanding new elections.
title: Thousands of Israelis join anti government protests

description: Turkey's local elections on Sunday were competitive and gave citizens many options but took place in a "starkly polarised environment" where more needs to be done to ensure freedom of expression, a European group of observers said on Monday.
title: Turkey election monitors say 'more needs to be done' to ensure freedom of expression

description: Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan said early on Monday that his ruling alliance did not achieve the desired result from Sunday's local elections, adding they would carry out self-criticism and address shortcomings.
title: Turkey's Erdogan says party to self-critique after local election losses

description: Ukraine's air force shot down two out of three Russia-launched Shahed drones overnight, Ukrainian military said on Monday.
title: Ukraine says it downed two of three Russian drones overnight

description: Russia has used five of its new hypersonic Zircon missiles to attack Kyiv since the start of the year, the city's military administration said on Monday.
title: Ukraine says Russia has fired five Zircon missiles at Kyiv this year

description: Recent Russian attacks have caused significant damage to the Ukrainian power system, but a total collapse is unlikely, the head of Ukraine's national grid company Ukrenergo Volodymyr Kudrytskyi said on Monday.
title: Ukraine's energy system far from collapse despite weeks of Russian strikes

description: The United States and Israel are expected to hold a virtual meeting on Monday to discuss the Biden administration's alternative proposals to an Israeli military invasion of Rafah, Axios reported on Sunday citing three Israeli and U.S. officials.
title: US and Israel to hold meeting on Rafah on Monday, Axios reports

description: An American aviation executive has had British judgments worth more than $4 million against him thrown out after a judge ruled that his legal opponent had covered up its use of hackers to steal the businessman’s emails in order to win the case.
title: US executive gets UK judgments thrown out after showing hackers swayed his case

description: Senior U.S. and Israeli officials planned to hold a virtual meeting on Monday to discuss the Biden administration's alternative proposals to an Israeli military invasion of Rafah, a U.S. official said.
title: US, Israeli officials to meet virtually on Rafah, US official says

description: The United States government is arranging a summit between President Joe Biden and his Japanese and South Korean counterparts in July, on the sidelines of a NATO summit in Washington, Japanese media outlets reported.
title: US plans trilateral summit with Japan, South Korea in July, Japanese media report

description: The U.S. State Department on Monday raised concerns about convictions of rights advocates in Vietnam, including five since January, and called on the country's government to respect freedoms of expression, association, and religion.
title: US raises concern over convictions of rights advocates in Vietnam
